our little secret, okay?

33:40.685 --> 33:42.225
The monster.

33:44.022 --> 33:45.572
The monster?

33:46.858 --> 33:49.028
He came after my dad died.

33:50.111 --> 33:52.201
<i>- I see.
- Hmm.</i>

33:53.156 --> 33:56.076
If you decide you want to
tell me what really happened...

33:56.618 --> 33:59.198
I'm gonna be here
to listen, okay?

34:04.668 --> 34:06.878
He said no one would believe me.

35:22.829 --> 35:23.829
Mommy.

35:56.029 --> 35:57.029
Walter.

35:59.658 --> 36:00.948
He's back.

36:05.246 --> 36:06.956
Is the monster gone?

36:07.290 --> 36:10.420
Now, Walter, you be sure and
put this back just like this.

36:25.600 --> 36:27.350
<i>Ow! Stop!</i>

36:42.409 --> 36:43.659
<i>Walter?</i>

36:45.286 --> 36:46.906
You didn't want to go outside?

36:53.795 --> 36:55.705
- What's that?
- Him.

36:56.506 --> 36:58.256
<i>- Him?
- The monster.</i>

37:03.638 --> 37:05.928
Laurie told me to draw it,
then we'll destroy it...

37:05.932 --> 37:07.432
And the monster's gonna go away.

37:09.436 --> 37:12.396
- Laurie that sits behind you?
- I'm gonna burn him up.

37:14.357 --> 37:15.937
Laurie said that her mom said

37:15.942 --> 37:17.532
to draw the things
that scared her...

37:17.902 --> 37:19.452
Then tear it up or burn it...

37:19.654 --> 37:20.954
And then it'll go away.

37:24.993 --> 37:26.083
That's Tyrone.

37:30.832 --> 37:31.832
Walter...

37:33.293 --> 37:34.843
Do you think I could, uh...

37:36.254 --> 37:37.594
talk to your mother sometime?

37:37.797 --> 37:38.837
What for?

37:38.840 --> 37:39.920
About the monster.

37:40.383 --> 37:41.763
Now, you've told her,
haven't you?

37:42.051 --> 37:44.891
She doesn't want to hear it.
She says we already moved once.

37:46.306 --> 37:49.516
You know, I don't think...

37:50.018 --> 37:52.308
That drawing these pictures
is really...

37:53.313 --> 37:55.323
the answer to your problem.

37:55.774 --> 37:59.534
But I think we can work
something out together, okay?

38:01.279 --> 38:02.279
Okay?

38:02.739 --> 38:03.909
<i>I guess so.</i>

38:04.824 --> 38:08.624
Good. I will see you
after recess.

38:09.788 --> 38:10.788
All right.

38:28.431 --> 38:29.431
Excuse me, guys.

38:30.767 --> 38:31.807
What happened to him?

38:32.227 --> 38:33.847
He was running in the building
after recess

38:33.853 --> 38:35.023
and fell down the stairs.

38:36.523 --> 38:37.863
Well, did somebody shove him?

38:38.233 --> 38:39.323
- No, he just fell.
- No?

38:39.692 --> 38:40.982
Sort of collapsed.

38:41.694 --> 38:42.994
But, you know,
it makes no sense.

38:43.404 --> 38:46.784
How do you break both arms
and legs falling down?

38:47.951 --> 38:49.831
Boy must've had weak bones.

39:25.196 --> 39:27.196
- Who is it?
- I'm Mr. Garvey.

39:27.198 --> 39:29.368
I'm one of Walter's
teachers from school.

39:39.085 --> 39:41.795
Uh... this fell.

39:42.964 --> 39:45.757
Thank you.
Is there a problem?

39:45.758 --> 39:49.678
- No, no, Mrs... miss...
- Miss.

39:50.305 --> 39:53.765
Miss Johnson, can I come in
and talk to you for a minute?

39:55.268 --> 39:56.478
Yes. I'm sorry.

39:56.853 --> 39:58.353
I'm gonna go throw something on.

40:17.415 --> 40:18.745
Damn.

40:24.797 --> 40:26.467
Miss Johnson,
I came to talk to you

40:26.674 --> 40:27.883
about your boy Walter.

40:27.884 --> 40:31.345
Because he seems to be having
some problems.

40:31.346 --> 40:32.386
Problems?

40:33.848 --> 40:34.638
Uh...

40:34.807 --> 40:38.597
Yeah. Perhaps because he
just recently changed schools.

40:39.228 --> 40:40.598
What kind of problems?

40:41.189 --> 40:43.439
I mean, all kids have problems,
don't they?

40:43.441 --> 40:46.321
That's what life is... problems.

40:46.945 --> 40:47.855
He got you good.

40:47.863 --> 40:49.413
Here, step into
the light for me?

40:49.697 --> 40:51.067
Oh, yeah. Um...

40:52.241 --> 40:56.741
Well, he seems to come to school
with a lot bruises, you know?

40:59.958 --> 41:01.288
Kind of banged up.

41:01.834 --> 41:03.214
The boy is clumsy.

41:03.586 --> 41:05.416
He's always falling
over somethin'.

41:06.047 --> 41:07.247
I don't know where he gets it.

41:07.799 --> 41:08.799
Not me.

41:10.176 --> 41:11.756
Certainly not me.

41:16.349 --> 41:18.229
Certainly not.

41:19.185 --> 41:20.265
But, uh...

41:21.020 --> 41:23.110
But he does seem to have
a strange...

41:23.773 --> 41:25.443
Preoccupation with monsters.

41:25.692 --> 41:27.942
<i>I mean, a monster
in particular...</i>

41:27.944 --> 41:31.034
<i>That he says
lives here in the house.</i>

41:31.280 --> 41:33.320
<i>It sounds silly, but...</i>

41:34.158 --> 41:35.158
Walter!

41:35.493 --> 41:38.078
Listen, there is no need
to bring Walter into this.

41:38.079 --> 41:39.079
Look!

41:39.664 --> 41:42.084
I've told that boy about
going on with these stories.

41:42.085 --> 41:43.633
I can't have it.
Walter!

41:44.002 --> 41:47.212
I said get your narrow behind
in this kitchen now!

41:47.588 --> 41:50.588
Miss Johnson,
I just came to talk to you.

41:53.678 --> 41:54.888
Get over here.

41:56.055 --> 41:57.555
What is your problem?

41:58.016 --> 41:59.636
Now, why the hell are you
going on

41:59.976 --> 42:02.186
